Sentencas: For the prospective use as micro-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (mu-SOFC) cathodes and for the investigation of reaction kinetics, La1 - xSrxCoO3 (LSCO) mixed ionic electronic conducting thin films were deposited by DC and RF sputtering onto a number of different substrate materials and characterized.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural characterization of interdigitated thin film La1-xSrcCoO3(LSCO) electrodes

Sentencas: Standard photolithographic and wet chemical etching methods were utilized to microstructure the LSCO films and XRD, SEM, AFM, WDS, and RBS were used to characterize their structure, topography, and chemistry.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural characterization of interdigitated thin film La1-xSrcCoO3(LSCO) electrodes

Sentencas: Sputtering resulted in very homogeneous and smooth thin crystalline films with Sr deficiency and submicron sized grains.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural characterization of interdigitated thin film La1-xSrcCoO3(LSCO) electrodes

Sentencas: Hydrochloric acid was found to readily etch LSCO with the etching quality strongly dependent on substrate material.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural characterization of interdigitated thin film La1-xSrcCoO3(LSCO) electrodes

Sentencas: LSCO films were most easily etched when deposited directly on silicon substrates, etched at intermediate rates when deposited on Gd:CeO2 films, and most resistant to etching after deposition onto single crystal yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ) substrates.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural characterization of interdigitated thin film La1-xSrcCoO3(LSCO) electrodes

Sentencas: Imperfect etching was attributed to interface formation and the presence of impurities.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural characterization of interdigitated thin film La1-xSrcCoO3(LSCO) electrodes
